title: Earth Science HiSET (Q25)
prompt: What information would be most useful to the scientist to find out why Rock Type B is most common at low tide?
feedback: The density of the rock types would be most useful to the scientist to find out why Rock Type B is most common at low tide. The density of the rocks might affect the ability of the tide to wash those rocks higher up on the shoreline, so this information would be relevant to answering the question. If the scientist finds that the rocks most common at low tide are denser, he might conclude that the density of the rock makes it difficult for the tide to wash those rocks higher up on the shoreline.
